## Data Type 2
# In a previous data type we will introduce data type like string,integer,float but
in this lecture we will introduce one more data type called boolean.
a = 10
b = 1.1
c = 'India'
d = True
e = False
print(type(a))                          <class'int'>
print(type(b))                          <class'float'>
print(type(c))                          <class'str'>
print(type(d))                          <class'bool'>
print(type(e))                          <class'bool'>
Notice carefully,the letter T in True and letter F in false
has to be capital otherwise it not not to be considered as Boolean.
As we are studied four data type let us tried some different, 
Which is called Data Conversion from one data type to another
a = int(5.7)
b = int('10')
print(a,type(a))                         5 <class'int'>
print(b,type(b))                        10 <class'int'>

a = str(5)
b = str(5.5)
print(a,type(a))                         5 <class'str'>
print(b,type(b))                        5.5 <class'str'>

a = float(7)
b = float('9')
print(a,type(a))                         7.0 <class'float'>
print(b,type(b))                        10.0 <class'float'>
# How type conversion in boolean data type:
a = bool(10)                             
b = bool(0)                             
c = bool(-10)   
print(a,type(a))                         True <class'bool'>
print(b,type(b))                        False <class'bool'>
print(c,type(c))                         True <class'bool'>
